h1. {color:#6366f1}Prompt2Test{color} — Phase 2 Roadmap

{tip:title=Feature Enhancements}
7 features to evolve Prompt2Test from a dev tool into a production-grade QA automation platform. Covers environment promotion, smart retries, suite execution, reporting, and VPN-friendly live browser.
{tip}

----

{toc:minLevel=2|maxLevel=3}

----

h2. Summary

|| # || Feature || Priority || Effort || Impact ||
| 1 | *Environment Promotion* — DEV -> QA -> UAT -> PROD | {status:colour=Green|title=SHIPPED} | {status:colour=Green|title=Done} | Trust model for higher environments |
| 2 | *Database Evaluation* — Aurora vs DynamoDB vs Hybrid | {status:colour=Yellow|title=P2} | 2-3 days | Cost, scale, and consistency optimization |
| 3 | *Failure Analysis & Logs* — screenshots, LLM root cause | {status:colour=Red|title=P0} | 5-7 days | Reduces debug time from 30 min to 2 min |
| 4 | *Report Generation* — PDF/HTML reports, trends | {status:colour=Yellow|title=P1} | 4-5 days | Stakeholder visibility, audit trail |
| 5 | *Tagging & Test Suites* — regression, smoke, deployment | {status:colour=Red|title=P0} | 3-4 days | Organize tests at scale, CI/CD integration |
| 6 | *Headless Suite + Smart Retry* — LLM retry, email alerts | {status:colour=Red|title=P0} | 7-10 days | CI/CD-grade automation platform |
| 7 | *noVNC via ALB* — HTTPS/443 for VPN compatibility | {status:colour=Yellow|title=P1} | 2.5 days | Corporate VPN users can see live browser |

