h2. Feature 3: Failure Analysis & Logs

h3. Capture on Failure

{section}
{column:width=33%}
{panel:title=Screenshot|borderColor=#dc2626|bgColor=#fff1f2}
Full-page screenshot at failure moment. Stored in S3. Displayed inline.
{panel}
{column}
{column:width=33%}
{panel:title=DOM Snapshot|borderColor=#dc2626|bgColor=#fff1f2}
Page HTML at failure time. Inspect elements without re-running.
{panel}
{column}
{column:width=33%}
{panel:title=Console & Network|borderColor=#dc2626|bgColor=#fff1f2}
Browser console + failed HTTP requests. Shows 404s, 500s, JS errors.
{panel}
{column}
{section}

h3. LLM Root Cause Analysis

{warning:title=On Failure — Automatic}
Send to Claude: failed step + error + screenshot (multimodal) + console errors + previous steps.
Claude returns: (a) probable root cause, (b) test issue vs app bug, (c) suggested fix.
{warning}

h3. New Fields

|| Field || Table || Description ||
| screenshot_s3_key | run_records | S3 key to failure screenshot |
| dom_snapshot_s3_key | run_records | S3 key to HTML DOM |
| console_logs | run_records | JSON array of console messages |
| network_errors | run_records | JSON array of failed requests |
| failure_analysis | run_records | LLM root cause text |
| failed_step_index | run_records | Which step failed |

